locality: Plants of Yemen. Al Mahra, Hawf Mts., NE of Hawf, second plateau, at spring near junction of tracks to Kon and the border with Oman.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. coastal mountains between Al Faydami and Hawf, plateau and slopes N of the village Damqawt. Small island of closed Anogeissus-woodland in the west of the Hawf forest, with e.g. Anogeissus, 6-8 (-10) m tall, Blepharispermum, Tamarindus, Acacia etbaica, Acacia senegalShrubs 1-2 m tall, with showy reddish flowers. [BGBM-Akz-Nr. 314-13-00-10]. Alt.: 520 m. 12.11.2000, Leg.: P. Hein, S. O. Bahah, M. Hubaishan, N. Kilian & C. Naumann PH 8078.

Yemen: Gov. Al-Mahra. coastal mountains between Al Faydami and Hawf, N of Jadib, steep slope with boulders (0.2-1 m diam.), directly below the J.Chatan escarpment, limestone rocks. Dense semidecidous woodland, the tree layer 5-10 m (e.g. Pistacia falcata, Olea), shrub layer 2-5 m tall, lianes, parasites, epiphytes and herbal layer. Alt.: 850-920 m. 13.11.2000, Leg.: P.
